        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Capabilities</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">Arqwell provides tailored CAD & automation services for architects and design teams. We deliver Rhino Python scripts, Dynamo routines, Revit family workflows, and model preparation services that reduce repetitive work and accelerate design development.</p>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">CAD Services — Narrative</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">We collaborate with clients to understand design intent and produce reliable automation: parametric layout tools, massing test-fits, scheduling-ready families, and model-cleanup scripts. Each engagement starts with a short scoping conversation to identify deliverables, file formats, and integration points with your current BIM workflows.</p>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">General Cost</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">Typical engagements vary by scope. As a high-level guideline:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-800 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Quick script / small task:</strong> $150–$500 — single script, small automation or dataset cleanup (1–3 days).</li>
          <li><strong>Feature / tool:</strong> $500–$2,500 — multi-step tool, Revit family set, or Rhino workflow (1–3 weeks).</li>
          <li><strong>Project integration / custom library:</strong> $2,500+ — larger integrations, scheduled deliveries, and documentation.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">Final cost depends on scope, testing requirements, and whether you need Revit/Rhino packaged families or additional QA. We provide a short proposal after our scoping call with a clearer timeline and deliverables.</p>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">CAD Vectorization</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">Based on the submitted RFQ form (<code>Arqwell RFQ Form — Submission.pdf</code>), we offer CAD vectorization services to convert scanned drawings, PDFs, or raster images into clean CAD geometry. Our standard rate is <strong>$300 per sheet</strong>. The process includes vector tracing, layer cleanup, attribute normalization, and a short QA pass to ensure dimensions align with the source.</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-800 space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li><strong>What we need:</strong> a clear scan or PDF of the sheet, notes on scale or a reference dimension, and any target file format (DWG, DXF, or Rhino).</li>
          <li><strong>Deliverables:</strong> vectorized CAD file, layers organized, and a short summary of edits.</li>
          <li><strong>Timing:</strong> typically 1–3 business days per sheet depending on complexity and queue.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">QA / QC Process</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">Arqwell follows a structured QA/QC workflow to ensure deliverables meet your standards. Our standard process includes:</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-800 space-y-1 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Initial review:</strong> assess submitted files for scale, legibility, and missing references.</li>
          <li><strong>Vectorization & cleanup:</strong> convert raster/PDF to vector, standardize layers and naming conventions.</li>
          <li><strong>Dimensional QA:</strong> check key dimensions against reference notes or a provided scale.</li>
          <li><strong>Consistency pass:</strong> ensure families/types, parameter names, and layer conventions follow the agreed standard.</li>
          <li><strong>Client review:</strong> deliver a review file and short QA report; incorporate one round of client feedback.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-3">If you have a detailed QA/QC checklist, upload it with your submission or email it to <a href="mailto:imani@isa-arqwell.com" class="underline">imani@isa-arqwell.com</a>. We include one round of feedback revisions in the standard price; additional QA rounds can be quoted separately.</p>

